results.name: a(n) = mu(prime(n)+1), where mu is the Moebius function.
link: Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, Moebius Function
xref: Cf. A049098 (primes p such that mu(p+1) = 0), A078329 (primes p such that mu(p+1) = -1), A089523 (primes p such that mu(p+1) = 1), A089451 (mu(p-1) for prime p), A089496 (mu(p+1)+mu(p-1) for prime p), A089497 (mu(p+1)-mu(p-1) for prime p).
